The paper proposes a method for analyzing the mobility of 3D shapes using deep neural networks. This involves joint analysis of motion part segmentation and motion attribute estimation, which suggests that the paper could belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) or graphics (cs.GR) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of deep neural networks indicates that the paper could also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the focus on mobility analysis suggests that the paper could also belong to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category.
